            <div  itemtype="http://schema.org/Article"  itemscope=""  class="item-page">
              <meta  content="en-GB"  itemprop="inLanguage" />
              <div  class="page-header">
                <h2  itemprop="name"> <a  itemprop="url"  href="Research.htm">
                    Project</a> </h2>
              </div>
              <div  class="article-info muted">
                <h1>Established Projects:</h1>
              </div>
              <div  itemprop="articleBody">
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <h3><span  class="style3">Soft Spheres sheared in 3D (SS3)</span></h3>
                    <table  style="height: auto; width: 675px;">
                      <tbody>
                        <tr>
                          <td><span  dir="ltr"></span><span  dir="ltr"></span><img
                               src="Research_files/SS3_paper_fig1.JPG"  style="width: auto; height: auto;" /></td>
                          <td  style="margin-left: 34px; width: 340px;">
                            <p  style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 100%;">Lastest:
                              "<a  style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255);"  href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B90Gj7g3sg_FQTFSdHAxcFFMQjA/view">Relaxation
                                and Residual Stress</a>" -- Presentation by JC
                              Tsai at APSDFD-2015(Boston USA)<br />
                              <span  style="font-family: Calibri,serif;"><span  lang="en-US"></span></span></p>
                            <p  style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 100%;"><span
                                 style="font-family: Calibri,serif;"><span  lang="en-US"><br />
                                </span></span></p>
                            <p  style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 100%;"> </p>
                            <p  style="margin-bottom: 0cm; line-height: 100%;">我
                              們建立了一個可以對顆粒系統施施以往復剪應變 (shearing)的系統。在第一階段 , 我們
                              將千餘顆將千餘顆 1cm
                              大小的球狀凝膠(hydrogel)，放進一對錐形邊界之間並填滿液體，將上錐來回旋轉，並記錄整個系統正向力與力矩隨時間的變化。同時，我們也採用內部攝影
                              (internal imaging)觀察材料裡面的動態。藉由研究軟顆粒在不同的體積濃度(Volume
                              Fraction)下的行為 , 我們希望對流變學研究(rheology)貢獻新的觀點......</p>
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                      </tbody>
                    </table>
                    <table  style="height: auto; width: 675px;">
                      <tbody>
                        <tr>
                          <td><br />
                          </td>
                          <td><br />
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                      </tbody>
                    </table>
                  </li>
                </ul>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <h3><span  class="style3">Granular Polymer with Transitions
                        (GPT)</span></h3>
                    <table  style="height: auto; width: 675px;">
                      <tbody>
                        <tr>
                          <td><span  dir="ltr"><a  href="http://www.phys.sinica.edu.tw/index_detail.php?id=research&amp;newsid=351"
                                 style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255);">物</a><a  href="http://www.phys.sinica.edu.tw/index_detail.php?id=research&amp;newsid=351"
                                 style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255);">理 所新聞稿</a><span
                                 style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255);"> </span>on </span><a
                               style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255);"  href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevLett.112.058001">our
                              previous work with a gradient of vibration</a><span
                               dir="ltr"> (Phys.Rev.Lett. 2014)<br />
                              <br />
                              <a  href="http://www.phys.sinica.edu.tw/jctsai/GPT2015/"
                                 style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255);">Demo movies +
                                孫宇岑's 2015 碩士論文</a><br />
                              <br />
                              Lastest: </span><a  href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B90Gj7g3sg_FSG85cHpFVHA5Q00/view?usp=sharing"><span
                                 style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255);">黃柏嘉's
                                presentation</span></a><span  dir="ltr"> at
                              APSDFD2015 [ppt]<br />
                              <br />
                              在之前我們所發表的論文(Phys. Rev. Lett. 112, 058001,
                              2014)中看到短珠鍊在空間梯度上運動行為分歧的現象。在透過攝影機進
                              一步研究珠鍊運動後，我們可將其分為3種
                              形態(見影片)。在固定震動強度下，珠鍊的跳動方式會自發的在不同形態之間轉變；同時隨著震動強度增加，各個形態會的比
                              例也會改變。同時我們也研究其型態與水平運動之間的關聯性…</span></td>
                          <td  style="margin-left: 34px; width: 340px;"><a  href="file:///W:/Lab_Construction_Service/website/jc_lab_web/Research_files/GPT_2015Fig01_setup.jpg"><img
                                 src="Research_files/GPT_2015Fig01_setup.jpg"  style="width: 337px; height: auto;" /></a></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                          <td><br />
                          </td>
                          <td><br />
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                      </tbody>
                    </table>
                  </li>
                </ul>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <h3><span  class="style3">Rotating two-Fluid Interface (RFI)
                      </span></h3>
                    <table  style="height: auto; width: 675px;">
                      <tbody>
                        <tr>
                          <td><span  dir="ltr"></span><span  dir="ltr"></span><img
                               src="Research_files/RFI_PRE_fig1.JPG"  style="width: 336px; height: auto;" /></td>
                          <td  style="margin-left: 34px; width: 340px;">
                            <p>Latest paper on "<a  style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255);"
                                 href="http://dx.doi.org/10.1103/PhysRevE.92.031002">vortex-induced
                                morphology</a>" (Phys. Rev. E 2005) </p>
                            <p><a  href="http://www.phys.sinica.edu.tw/jctsai/vortex/"><span
                                   style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255);">Artistic
                                  pictures &amp; demo movies</span></a></p>
                            <span  dir="ltr">這是由實驗室的前成員-賴靜
                              瑤所開啟的研究(最早可追溯至2009年的國際高中科展)，觀察液體界面隨著上蓋轉速變化
                              所產生出耐人尋味的形貌。為了解釋此現象我們同時觀察了內部流場的結構，來理解界面產生
                              ”plateau”的緣故。</span></td>
                        </tr>
                      </tbody>
                    </table>
                    <table  style="height: auto; width: 675px;">
                      <tbody>
                        <tr>
                          <td><br />
                          </td>
                          <td><br />
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                      </tbody>
                    </table>
                  </li>
                  <br />
                </ul>
                <h1><span  style="color: rgb(192, 192, 192);"></span><span  style="color: rgb(192, 192, 192);">Developing
                    Projects:</span></h1>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <h3><span  class="style3">Granular Polymer in Virtual
                        experiments (GPV) </span></h3>
                  </li>
                </ul>
                <table  style="height: auto; margin-left: 30px; width: 675px;">
                  <tbody>
                    <tr>
                      <td><span  dir="ltr">--- Numerical simulations analogous
                          to GPT<br />
                          --- Minimal model: 1d, dashpot coupling<br />
                          --- Spontaneous switching in GPT reproduced</span></td>
                      <td  style="text-align: center;"><img  style="width: 267px; height: auto;"
                           src="Research_files/GPV_energy_potential.png" /><br />
                      </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                      <td><br />
                      </td>
                      <td><br />
                      </td>
                    </tr>
                  </tbody>
                </table>
                <ul>
                  <li>
                    <h3><span  class="style3">Floating Disks with Jamming (FDJ)</span></h3>
                    <table  style="height: auto; width: 675px;">
                      <tbody>
                        <tr>
                          <td><span  dir="ltr">--- <a  style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255);"
                                 href="Research_files/demo_FDC_Setup_in_action_V_20150311_175852.mp4">continuous
                                cyclic driving</a> [Movie]<br />
                              --- airbed eliminating substrate friction<br />
                              --- <a  style="color: rgb(51, 102, 255);"  href="Research_files/demo_FDC_20150306_01_600fps_test_by_hand_JC_%7B1s_in_20s%7DMPEG4v3.avi">Bi-refringent
                                disks demonstrating force-chains, despite the
                                fluidity</a> [Movie]<br />
                            </span></td>
                          <td><img  src="Research_files/FDJ_demo.jpg"  style="width: auto; height: 244px;" /></td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                          <td><br />
                          </td>
                          <td><br />
                          </td>
                        </tr>
                      </tbody>
                    </table>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <h3>Hydro-dynamical Particle Synthesis (HPS)</h3>
                    <table  style="height: auto; width: 675px;">
                      <tbody>
                        <tr>
                          <td><span  dir="ltr">--- Production of soft spheres
                              using interfacial instabilities<br />
                              --- Size and Elasticity adjustable<br />
                            </span></td>
                        </tr>
                      </tbody>
                    </table>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    <h3>Soft Ball Dynamics (SBD)<br />
                      <span  class="style3"></span></h3>
                    <table  style="height: auto; width: 675px;">
                      <tbody>
                        <tr>
                          <td><span  dir="ltr">--- Microscopic experiments for
                              deriving the intrinsic timescales of packed grains
                              discovered in SS3.<br />
                            </span></td>
                        </tr>
                      </tbody>
                    </table>
                  </li>
                </ul>
                <p><br />
                </p>
                <p>We are particularly interested in hearing students' thoughts,
                  opinions,or even tentative proposals regarding our ongoing
                  projects. Please don't hesitate to include them in your
                  application materials to help the selection committee have a
                  better understanding about you. Feel free to stop by our lab
                  (Room-232, Phone: 2789-8914/8917) and talk to us if you are
                  interested</p>
              </div>
